`useMemo` memoizes the *result* of a function calculation, returning a cached value. `useCallback` memoizes the *function definition* itself, preventing it from being recreated on every render. Use `useMemo` for expensive computations, and `useCallback` when passing callbacks to optimized child components to prevent unnecessary renders.

```javascript
const value = useMemo(() => computeValue(a), [a]);
const handler = useCallback(() => doSomething(b), [b]);
```
